    "top_line": "STAMPEDE: adding 2yr abiraterone to ADT+RT in high-risk M0 prostate cuts MFS (HR 0.53) and OS (HR 0.60); enzalutamide adds nothing.",
    "tldr": "Prostate carried the day. A pooled STAMPEDE analysis moves 2yr abiraterone onto the ADT+RT backbone for high-risk M0 disease (6-yr MFS 82% vs 69%). RT was mandated for N0, so this is the curative population radoncs already treat; adding enzalutamide gave no incremental MFS.",
